					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 90 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Mahādēva at Tirumaṟaikkāḍu, by a certain <hi rend="bold">Śiṟiyāṉ Kuvāvaṉ</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Uttuṅgatuṅga-Pallavaraiyaṉ</hi> of Kōṭṭūr in Nenmali-nāḍu. The donor was probably a chief who got his designation after the title <hi rend="italic">Uttuṅgatuṅga</hi> of his overlord the king.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
